## Resource Development Pattern
When adding a new resource (e.g., Files, Users):

1. **Create Test File**:
```ruby
# spec/mangoapps/resources/files_spec.rb
RSpec.describe "MangoApps::Client::Files" do
  let(:client) { MangoApps::Client.new(config) }

  before do
    allow(client).to receive(:access_token)
      .and_return(double(token: "testtoken"))
  end

  it "lists files" do
    stub_request(:get, "https://yourdomain.mangoapps.com/api/files")
      .with(headers: { "Authorization" => "Bearer testtoken" })
      .to_return(status: 200, body: { "files" => [] }.to_json)

    res = client.files_list
    expect(res).to include("files")
  end
end
```

2. **Create Resource Module**:
```ruby
# lib/mangoapps/resources/files.rb
module MangoApps
  class Client
    module Files
      def files_list(params = {})
        get("files", params: params)
      end
    end
  end
end
```

3. **Include in Main Module**:
```ruby
# lib/mangoapps.rb
require "mangoapps/resources/files"
MangoApps::Client.include(MangoApps::Client::Files)
```

